@node MEMORY "CSV-Tool Help:  MEMORY"
@smartwrap
@font helvetica.font 13
@{jleft}@{lindent 8}

@{Title_Header "M E M O R Y"}
@{Title_String "Memory requirements to"}
@{Title_Footer "run this program stable."}


  @{bold "M"}ake sure that your Operating System and Workbench
is of the Version @{bold "39.x"} or higher.@{PAR}
You defintily need a minimum of @{bold "800.000 bytes"} of Memory
to run this program @{bold "(import-, and export document are stored in memory)"}.
@{white "CHIP"}-Ram and @{white "FAST"}-Ram are usable.@{PAR}
@{pard}

@endnode

@node DOCUMENTS "CSV-Tool Help:  DOCUMENTS"
@smartwrap
@font helvetica.font 13
@{jleft}@{lindent 8}

@{Title_Header "D O C U M E N T S"}
@{Title_String "General existing restrictions"}
@{Title_Footer "on the document managment."}


  @{bold "T"}he program can not handle documents with more
than @{bold "255 characters per line"} in general. More
than @{bold "26 columnes"} can't be handled because
of the limitation by use of alphabetical variable
names (e. g. @{bold "[CELL_A] --> [CELL_Z]"}).@{par}
@{pard}

@endnode

